Ok, I love Gluten Free Games, and this is no exception. But since it is new, it still has a lot of glitches. One of the biggest glitches is that you have to unlock the next dog before you are able to play as a dog. For example, I had to unlock the beagle before I was able to play as the German shepherd. Next, some of the dogs graphics are not the best. Like when the Great Dane runs, the back legs cross over and it looks weird. And when the German Sheperd jumps, it jumps way too high.  Another thing is that the prey animals spawn way to much. Like when I walk out of my house, there are like 6 different prey animals out there. It should be harder to find and catch your prey. Next, the world is really big, but not that interesting. There is not that much vegetation, or even buildings. It would be nice if you added more texture to the game. This game is great so far, it just needs some improvement. The only reason I rate this 4 stars is because there are glitches. When they are fixed I will rate this 5 stars. If you are reading this and wondering if you should get the game or not then you should totally get the game. I know I said there are a lot of glitches, but it is still amazing. And the game will continue to be updated.

content: It's very good, however.. there are some bugs that need to be fixed. 1. In the upgrades and buffs section it says 'Hiss' and 'Meow'. This is probably something you forgot to change, but that's totally ok because we'll make mistakes, and it really isn't that important but some people might get annoyed with it so it would be best to fix it. 2. The Great Dane's legs go all weird when you attack/pick up something. 3. It doesn't let me play the dog I unlock. For example: we have two starting dogs, (Dane and shepherd)but we can only play as one (the Dane) until we become level 5, but when we become lvl 5 we can't play as the beagle even though it says to unlock it at lvl 5. Long story short, the dog unlocking is a bit messed up. 4. (This isn't really a bug but it's still annoying) when trying to get over a sidewalk, you always have to jump to get on it, if you don't your dog gets stuck. 5. Maybe make it so all dogs appear more often? Because I tend to have trouble finding dogs of the same breed as me. OTHERWISE, this game is splendid, however I will love it more if most of these bugs are fixed. I am very excited for more simulators in the future!
